      "content": "# actions become operations after dispatch adding metadata\n\nThe distinction between actions and operations is fundamental to the Powerhouse document model:\n\n- **Action** — A proposed change. A JSON object with `type` (action name) and `input` (payload). This is what you dispatch.\n- **Operation** — A completed change. Contains the original action plus system metadata: `index`, `timestamp`, `hash`, and optional `error`.\n\nActions become operations after dispatch through `addActions`. The system appends metadata that enables event sourcing — the index provides ordering, the hash enables integrity verification, and the timestamp records when it happened.\n\nSince [[operation errors are recorded on operations not thrown to callers]], even failed actions produce operations (with the error captured in the `error` field).\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[architecture decisions]]\n- [[reducer patterns]]",
